She said oh I’ll get more and I said no thank you. Two minutes later a gentleman slammed water on my table stating here is your water. I should have followed my first mind to exit however, because I live in the building I wanted to give it a try in the event I could dine there out of convenience. Unfortunately, that will never happen. Here’s why: My food arrived and the rude waitress asked if I wanted anything else. Well I asked for skim milk and received whole milk however, based on her response to the bug in my water I made no effort to exchange for skim milk. Finally, I asked for butter and syrup for my pancakes. I received butter and syrup which I promptly put on my pancakes. Noting a strange taste, I realized the waitress had given me a bottle of sugar free syrup. When I asked if they had regular syrup she seemed quite confused. At this point it was strike 3, I asked for the check, paid it quickly and decided never to grace the doors of Eggs Inc. ever again even though I can roll out of bed and be there in 2 minutes. Extreme disappointed in my order. I came to this place as a had a doctor's appointment during my lunch time (I'm 8mths pregnant with twins). I get my food & take an Uber back to the office; super excited to try out the salad as it looked like it would be yummy based on the menu & aside from starving. I get to the office, opened up my meal & was completely disappointed as it was nothing like what it read on the menu. The salad didn't have mandarins or strawberries, it had blue cheese (which I don't eat), dried cranberries & it also had tomato which I don't mind but it was not on the menu. I paid $15 (because I added chicken for a salad I couldn't eat since it had crumbled blue cheese all over. It's not like I could take it off.
